			"notes": {
				"569c623e-0344-4a19-ab52-bda2b59c5d6d": {
					"title": "Tavern Mimic Brain",
					"text": "<div class=\"Basic-Text-Frame stat-block-background one-column-stat\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Lair Actions.</strong>&nbsp;On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the tavern mimic takes one of the following lair actions; the mimic can&rsquo;t take the same lair action two rounds in a row.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><strong>Drool.</strong></em>&nbsp;The tavern mimic secretes acid from a part of its ceiling in a&nbsp;<strong>30-foot square</strong>. Each creature directly under the area must make a&nbsp;<strong>DC16 Dexterity saving throw</strong>, taking <strong>14&nbsp;(4d6)&nbsp;</strong>acid damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><strong>Peristalsis</strong></em>. A wave shudders through the tavern mimic as its hidden musculature contracts. Each non-mimic creature in the tavern must make a <strong>DC16&nbsp;</strong><strong>Dexterity saving throw.</strong>&nbsp;On a failure, a creature is pushed&nbsp;<strong>15 feet</strong>&nbsp;in a direction of the tavern mimic&rsquo;s choice, where it falls&nbsp;<strong>prone</strong>&nbsp;and takes <strong>14&nbsp;(4d6)&nbsp;</strong>bludgeoning damage. On a success, it is moved 5 feet in a direction of the tavern mimic&rsquo;s choice, takes no damage, and doesn&rsquo;t fall prone.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><strong>Sink</strong></em>. A&nbsp;<strong>10-foot square</strong>&nbsp;of the tavern mimic&rsquo;s floor becomes incredibly soft and sticky for the next&nbsp;<strong>minute</strong>. Each creature on the floor in the area, or that enters the area for the first time on its turn, must succeed on a <strong>DC16&nbsp;</strong><strong>Strength saving throw</strong>&nbsp;or become&nbsp;<strong>restrained</strong>. A creature that ends its turn while restrained in this way sinks&nbsp;<strong>2 feet</strong>&nbsp;into the tavern&rsquo;s floor and takes <strong>14&nbsp;(4d6)&nbsp;</strong>acid damage. A creature that sinks below its height can&rsquo;t breathe.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">A creature within&nbsp;<strong>5 feet</strong>&nbsp;of a creature restrained in this way, including the restrained creature, can make a <strong>DC16&nbsp;</strong><strong>Strength</strong>&nbsp;check, freeing the stuck creature and pulling it to the nearest non-sinking area on a success. The area is difficult terrain for all non-mimic creatures until the tavern mimic finishes a short or long rest.</span></p>\n</div>",
					"plain": "Lair Actions.On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the tavern mimic takes one of the following lair actions; the mimic cant take the same lair action two rounds in a row.Drool.The tavern mimic secretes acid from a part of its ceiling in a30-foot square. Each creature directly under the area must make aDC16 Dexterity saving throw, taking 14(4d6)acid damage on a failure, or half as much damage on a success.Peristalsis. A wave shudders through the tavern mimic as its hidden musculature contracts. Each non-mimic creature in the tavern must make a DC16Dexterity saving throw.On a failure, a creature is pushed15 feetin a direction of the tavern mimics choice, where it fallsproneand takes 14(4d6)bludgeoning damage. On a success, it is moved 5 feet in a direction of the tavern mimics choice, takes no damage, and doesnt fall prone.Sink. A10-foot squareof the tavern mimics floor becomes incredibly soft and sticky for the nextminute. Each creature on the floor in the area, or that enters the area for the first time on its turn, must succeed on a DC16Strength saving throwor becomerestrained. A creature that ends its turn while restrained in this way sinks2 feetinto the taverns floor and takes 14(4d6)acid damage. A creature that sinks below its height cant breathe.A creature within5 feetof a creature restrained in this way, including the restrained creature, can make a DC16Strengthcheck, freeing the stuck creature and pulling it to the nearest non-sinking area on a success. The area is difficult terrain for all non-mimic creatures until the tavern mimic finishes a short or long rest.",
					"player": true,
					"statBlock": true,
					"id": "569c623e-0344-4a19-ab52-bda2b59c5d6d"
				}
			}
